modules.description: This module offers operations for managing maps with code point keys and generic values, enabling efficient insertion, deletion, lookup, and traversal. It includes functions for searching, filtering, and transforming bindings, leveraging ordered comparisons for structured data manipulation. Use cases include processing Unicode character mappings or other scenarios requiring precise code point-based associations.

Provides functions to parse and query Unicode character data from XML, including properties like name, category, and block. Works with structured data derived from Unicode's XML files, such as character records and property maps. Enables tasks like character classification, name lookup, and block-based filtering.

Provides efficient management of code point-based mappings with support for insertion, deletion, lookup, and traversal. Offers functions to search, filter, and transform bindings using ordered comparisons for structured data handling. Can process Unicode character mappings or similar data requiring precise code point associations. Examples include extracting properties for specific characters or building lookup tables for character classification.
